1. Core Architecture Setup

Frontend (Admin UI) → built in React (your mockup).

Backend (Admin API Layer) → Node.js / Express / NestJS (recommended) running at api-admin.bhoomy.in.

Databases & Services (already in your system):

MariaDB → stores sites, users, ads, payments, logs.

Elasticsearch → search index & analytics.

Crawler → Node.js scripts handling crawling.

MyPay → UPI transactions & billing.

AdNet → Ads campaigns, impressions, clicks.

The Admin API Layer acts as the bridge between the UI and these services.



7. Security Layer

Because admin.bhoomy.in is very sensitive:

JWT-based authentication with role checks (admin, moderator).

2FA login (Google Authenticator / SMS OTP).

IP whitelisting or VPN requirement (only office/staff IPs can log in).

HTTPS everywhere (Let’s Encrypt certs).

Separate DB users for admin with limited permissions (no root).

🔹 8. Making it the “Single Control Center”

Your Admin UI (React) only talks to Admin API.
The Admin API then:

Queries MariaDB for sites/users/ads/payments.

Queries Elasticsearch for search/index data.

Calls crawler services to start/stop jobs.

Talks to MyPay service for transactions.

Manages AdNet campaigns.









